message.raw:
- New trimesh box collision function from scratch.
- Opcode internal support for double precision vertices in meshinterface.
- Opcode vc++ project file modified.
- Drawstuff now has double precision dsDrawTriangle()
- Fixed some small trimesh problems.

When colliding with a plane, the contact points were generated as if the
length was multplied by 2.
The only thing needed to correct this is to devide lhz by 2.

If a user geometry class is created before any call to dxGeom's constructor
then when initColliders inside dxGeom gets called it erases over the user
defined class. This patch fixes that. Contributed by Daniel Duhprey.
